(66, 'mia.villarica@gmail.com', 'LAS_Q4W2_Reading-and-Lit_Redeveloped-V3with-illus-layout.pdf', 'uploads/786637409550494d82cbf543687649ea.pdf', '2025-03-23 15:59:46', '1\nKuwa rter 4\nGawaing Pampagkatuto\nLinggo\n2\nsa Reading at Literacy\nGawaing Pampagkatuto sa Reading and Literacy 1\nKuwarter 4: Linggo 2\nAng materyal na ito ay gagamitin lamang para sa pagtuturo ng mga guro at\npagkatuto ng mga mag-aaral sa MATATAG K to 10 Kurikulum. Layunin nitong maging batayan\nsa paghahatid ng mga nilalaman, pamantayan, at kasanayang pampagkatuto ng kurikulum.\nIpinagbabawal ang anumang hindi awtorisadong pagkopya, pagrebisa, paggamit o pagbahagi\nng materyal na ito. Anumang paglabag o hindi pagsunod sa itinakdang saklaw ay maaaring\nmagresulta sa kaparusahan alinsunod sa legal na hakbang.\nAng ilan sa mga akdang ginamit sa materyal na ito ay orihinal. Pinagsumikapan ng\nmga bumuo ng materyal na makuha ang pahintulot ng mga manunulat sa paggamit ng iba\npang akda at hindi inaangkin ang karapatang-ari ng mga ito.\nTiniyak din ang kawastuhan ng mga impormasyong nasa materyal na ito. Para sa mga\nkatanungan o puna, maaaring sumangguni sa Tanggapan ng Direktor ng Bureau of Learning\nResources sa pamamagitan ng pagtawag sa mga numerong (02) 8634-1072 / 8631-6922 o\npagpapadala ng email sa blr.od@deped.gov.ph.\nMula sa Kagawaran ng Edukasyon, isang taos pusong pasasalamat sa United States\nAgency for International Development and RTI International sa pamamagitan ng ABC+ Project\nat UNICEF sa pagsuporta at pagbibigay ng teknikal na tulong sa pagbuo ng MATATAG\nlearning resources.\nInilathala ng Kagawaran ng Edukasyon\nKalihim: Sonny M. Angara\nPangalawang Kalihim: Gina O. Gonong\nBumuo sa Pagsusulat\nManunulat: Anne Sheila T. Choi\nTagasuri: Briget V. Varron, Aisa Veronica Pintor\nTagaguhit: Fermin Fabella\nTaglapat: Rejoice Ann C. Mananquil\nNamahala sa Pagbuo ng Materyal\nBureau of Curriculum Development\nBureau of Learning Delivery\nBureau of Learning Resources\nDepartment of Education – Bureau of Learning Resources (DepEd- BLR)\nOffice Address: Ground Floor, Bonifacio Building, DepEd Complex\nMeralco Avenue, Pasig City\nPhilippines 1600\nTelefax: (02) 8634-1054; 8634-1072; 8631-4985\nEmail Address: blr.lrqad@deped.gov.ph; blr.lrpd@deped.gov.ph\nMGA PAHINANG GAWAING PAMPAGKATUTO\nAsignatura Reading and Markahan 4\nLiteracy\nLinggo 4 Araw 2\nPamagat/Paksa Malikhaing Gawain mula sa Binasang\nng Aralin Alamat\nPangalan Baitang at\nSeksiyon\nGawain Blg. 1.1\nPamagat/Paksa ng Aralin: Malikhaing Gawain mula sa\nBinasang Alamat\nLayunin: Tukuyin ang elemento ng kuwento\nKagamitang Kailangan: Lapis\nLaang-panahon para sa gawain: 5 minuto\nPanuto: Tukuyin ang mga elemento ng kuwentong “Ang\nAlamat ni Mariang Sinukuan”\n1\nSTORY MAP\nPamagat: Tauhan: Tagpuan:\nSimula: Gitna: Huli:\nAssessment/Reflection:\n• Indicate how the learners will be assessed on their\nunderstanding or completion of the activity.\n• Ang pagtataya sa gawain ay maaaring\nmapuntusan sa pamamagitan ng pasalitang\nsagot o sa pamamaraang paggamit ng lapis at\npapel.\n2\nKumpletuhin ang pangungusap:\n⚫ Ito ang mga dapat isama sa muling pagkuwento:\n_____, _____, at _____.\nNotes for Facilitators: Provide any notes, direction, or\nguidance for teachers or facilitators who will be\nconducting the activity.\nPara sa mga guro: Bigyan ng kaukulang oras ang mga\nmag-aaral para makapag-isip at makapaghanda\nkasama ng kanilang mga kapares.\nExtension/Differentiation (if applicable): Suggest ways to\nextend the activity for advanced learners or to\ndifferentiate for various skill levels.\n3\nMGA PAHINANG GAWAING PAMPAGKATUTO\nAsignatura Reading and Markahan 4\nLiteracy\nLinggo 2 Araw 3\nPamagat/Paksa Pagsunod-sunod sa mga pangyayari sa\nng Aralin alamat\nPangalan Baitang at\nSeksiyon\nGawain Blg. 2.1\nPamagat/Paksa ng Aralin: Pagsunod-sunod ng\npangyayari\nLayunin: Sequence events in a story\nKagamitang Kailangan: Lapis\nLaang-panahon para sa gawain: 5 minuto\nPanuto: Lagyan ng bilang ang mga kahon sa ilalim ng\nmga larawan ayon sa pagkakasunod-sunod sa kuwento.\n4\nGawain Blg. 2.2\nPamagat/Paksa ng Aralin: Salitang Naglalarawan\nLayunin: Identify the describing words in the given\nsentences.\nKagamitang Kailangan: Lapis\nLaang-panahon para sa gawain: 5 minuto\nPanuto: Basahin ang bawat pangungusap at tukuyin ang\nsalitang naglalarawan sa lugar, bagay, kilos, o sitwasyon.\nBilugan ang salitang naglalarawan sa pangungusap\n1. Ang malawak na parke ay puno ng mga naglalaro at\nnamamasyal.\n2. Si Lani ay may makulay na bag na paborito niyang\ndalhin sa eskuwela.\n3. Mabilis na tumakbo si Jorge upang makahabol sa dyip.\n4. Ang tahimik na silid-aklatan ay isang magandang\nlugar para mag-aral.\n5. Masaya ang mga bata nang dumating ang kanilang\nmga magulang sa programa.\nAssessment/Reflection:\n• Indicate how the learners will be assessed on their\nunderstanding or completion of the activity.\n5\n• Ang pagtataya sa gawain ay maaaring\nmapuntusan sa pamamaraang paggamit ng lapis\nat papel.\nKumpletuhin ang pangungusap:\n⚫ Ang mga salitang naglalarawan ay maaring\nmaglarawan ng______.\n⚫ Ang isang salitang naglalarawan na natutuhan ko\nngayong araw ay ____.\nNotes for Facilitators: Provide any notes, direction, or\nguidance for teachers or facilitators who will be\nconducting the activity.\nPara sa mga guro: Bigyan ng kaukulang oras ang mga\nmag-aaral para makapag-isip.\nExtension/Differentiation (if applicable): Suggest ways to\nextend the activity for advanced learners or to\ndifferentiate for various skill levels.\nPara sa mga mabilis magtrabaho, maaari silang magsulat\nng sarili nilang pangungusap at tukuyin ang salitang\nnaglalarawang ginamit nila.\n6\nMGA PAHINANG GAWAING PAMPAGKATUTO\nAsignatura Reading and Markahan 4\nLiteracy\nLinggo 2 Araw 4\nPamagat/Paksa Pagsulat ng liham\nng Aralin\nPangalan Baitang at\nSeksiyon\nGawain Blg. 2.1\nPamagat/Paksa ng Aralin: Pagsulat ng liham\nLayunin: Write words correctly and legibly.\nKagamitang Kailangan: Lapis\nLaang-panahon para sa gawain: 5 minuto\nPanuto: Punan ng tamang salita sa patlang upang\nmakabuo ng isang liham sa kaibigan.\nMaaring pumili sa mga salitang ito, o sumulat ng ibang\nangkop na salita:\npagbaha maitutulong bagong kumot pinsala\nkaibigan kumusta\n7\nPetsa: _____________________________\nMahal kong _________________________,\n__________________________ ka na? Nabalitaan kong\nnagkaroon ng matinding _______________ sa lugar ninyo.\nSana ay hindi naman naging malaki ang\n___________________ ng pagbaha sa inyo. Sabihan mo\nlang ako kung mayroon akong __________________ sa inyo.\nPupunta raw diyan si Nanay para abutan kayo ng\n_____________________.\nNagmamahal,\n____________________\nAssessment/Reflection:\n• Indicate how the learners will be assessed on their\nunderstanding or completion of the activity.\n• Ang pagtataya sa gawain ay maaaring\nmapuntusan sa pamamaraang paggamit ng lapis\nat papel.\n8\nKumpletuhin ang pangungusap:\n⚫ Ang mga bahagi ng isang liham pangkaibigan ay :\n____________________________________\nNotes for Facilitators: Provide any notes, direction, or\nguidance for teachers or facilitators who will be\nconducting the activity.\nPara sa mga guro: Bigyan ng kaukulang oras ang mga\nmag-aaral para makapag-isip.\nExtension/Differentiation (if applicable): Suggest ways to\nextend the activity for advanced learners or to\ndifferentiate for various skill levels.\nPara sa mga mabilis magtrabaho, maaari silang magsulat\nng sarili nilang pangungusap at tukuyin ang salitang\nnaglalarawang ginamit nila.\nRemember that the format of a learning activity sheet can be adjusted to fit the needs of your\nlearners, the subject matter, and the level of detail required. The key is to provide clear\ninstructions, engaging tasks, and the necessary resources to help learners achieve the\nintended learning outcomes.\n9\n', 0),
(67, 'mia.villarica@gmail.com', 'Ship-Handling-and-Maneuvering-Midterm-Assignment.pdf', 'uploads/fb2768cbf5d04beb8468d8545ab2c5b0.pdf', '2025-03-23 16:07:36', 'BELLING, Michelle L.\nMT109 - MET302 Captain Rolando Jr Magnaye\n1.) List down safety precautions that should be taken when anchoring a vessel.\nWhen anchoring a vessel, several safety precautions should be observed to ensure the safety of\nthe vessel, its crew, and the surrounding environment. Prior to anchoring, a thorough risk analysis\nshould be conducted, taking into account factors such as wind strength, tidal movements, potential\nunderwater hazards like cables and pipelines, and the nature of the seabed. The anchor and chain\nmust be of sufficient strength and appropriate for the vessel and the area of operation. It is crucial to\navoid anchoring in prohibited areas like shipping channels or transit lanes and never tie vessels to\nnavigational aids. Furthermore, vessels should maintain a safe distance from other ships, considering\ntheir maneuverability in case of anchor dragging, with a recommended distance of no less than one\nnautical mile from the nearest grounding line.\nDuring the anchoring operation, lower the anchor to the bottom rather than throwing it overboard to\nprevent tangling. The length of the anchor line should be at least three times the depth of the water,\nincreasing to five times in rough seas. Monitor the anchor to ensure it is not dragging by regularly\nchecking the rope tension and the vessel\'s position17. After anchoring, verify that the chain becomes\nslack and tight again for several cycles to confirm the anchor is holding. In deeper waters, over 20\nmeters, the anchor should be lowered close to the seabed before releasing it to prevent damage. Avoid\ndropping anchor from the stern or midship to prevent swamping the vessel1. Always be prepared to\nheave up the anchor and re-anchor if dragging occurs, and consider keeping the main engine on\nstandby in case of uncertain weather conditions or proximity to other vessels.\n2.) Discuss the importance of communication among crew members during the anchoring\nprocess.\nEffective communication among crew members is essential during the anchoring process, directly\nimpacting the safety and efficiency of the operation. Anchoring involves multiple individuals, including\nbridge team members and the forecastle team, each with specific responsibilities that must be\ncoordinated. Clear and concise communication ensures everyone is aware of the plan, their roles, and\nany potential hazards. This is especially critical given that anchoring environments often involve high\nnoise levels, significant distances between crew members, and a need for precise execution. Proper\ncommunication minimizes misunderstandings, facilitates quick responses to changing conditions, and\nultimately prevents accidents.\nTo achieve effective communication, standard phrases and agreed-upon signals should be used to\nsimplify the process and reduce confusion. The officer in charge at the anchor station must maintain\nopen communication with the bridge, providing regular updates on the anchor\'s position and the status\nof the operation. This includes reporting critical factors such as the number of shackles lowered and\nany issues encountered. Furthermore, pre-planning meetings or \"huddles\" to discuss the anchoring\nplan, assign tasks, and address potential contingencies are essential for seamless coordination.\nEncouraging active listening and ensuring crew members feel heard and understood further enhances\ncommunication effectiveness, contributing to a safer and more successful anchoring evolution.\nReferences:\nAlandia. (n.d.). Safe mooring - Anchoring: Anchoring Principles.\nhttps://alandia.com/article/safe-anchoring/\nBluewater Cruising Association. (2015, April 22). Effective Communication on Board - Currents\nBluewater Cruising. https://currents.bluewatercruising.org/articles/effective-communication-board/\nBritannia P&I Club. (2014, December 1). Safe anchoring & mooring procedures.\nhttps://britanniapandi.com/2014/12/safe-mooring-and-anchoring/\nCommunication between helm and crew when anchoring. Great Escape. (n.d.).\nhttps://www.greatescape.co.nz/sailing-tips/communication-between-helm-and-crew-when-anchoring/\nMarine Digital. (n.d.). Ship Anchor and Ship Anchoring Methods - Marine Digital.\nhttps://marine-digital.com/article\\_ship\\_anchoring\\_methods\nMaritime Safety Victoria. (n.d.). Anchoring. Handbook.safetransport.vic.gov.au. Retrieved from\nhttps://handbook.safetransport.vic.gov.au/boating-rules/basic-boat-handling-tips/anchoring/\nOwaysonline. (2025, February 7). Safe Anchorage / Anchor Planning with Diagram & Explanation.\nhttps://owaysonline.com/anchoring/\nSAFETY4SEA. (2024, December 23). The three phases of anchoring procedure - SAFETY4SEA.\nhttps://safety4sea.com/cm-the-three-phases-of-anchoring-procedure/\nSAFETY4SEA. (2024, December 30). Tips for efficient and safe anchoring.\nhttps://safety4sea.com/cm-tips-for-efficient-and-safe-anchoring/\nShipowners\' Club. (2022, March 2). Guidance on Anchoring.\nhttps://www.shipownersclub.com/latest-updates/publications/guidance-anchoring/\nSkuld. (2019, June 4). Good anchoring practice.\nhttps://www.skuld.com/topics/ship/safety/good-anchoring-practice/\nTeam, M. I. (2024, March 4). Responsibilities of Deck Officer During Anchoring Operation. Marine\nInsight.\nhttps://www.marineinsight.com/marine-navigation/responsibilities-deck-officer-anchoring-operations/\n', 0),
